                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Choate reports that Lord Lansdowne verbally protested emphatically to the
                    Russian Ambassador on the 10th instant against treatment by his Government as
                    absolutely contraband, without considering destination, articles which are
                    generally considered so only conditionally, aggravated by their harsh mode of
                    enforcing their contention by sinking neutral ships carrying such articles
                    without giving them a hearing.)</p>
            </div>
